description:
## Bug Report

Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)

Hi,

The following test case triggers an unexpected error:
```
CREATE TABLE t0(c0 DOUBLE );
CREATE TABLE t1 LIKE t0;
CREATE INDEX i0 ON t1(c0 ASC);
ALTER TABLE t1  CHANGE c0 c0 DOUBLE NOT NULL ;
SET @a = 0.7481117056976476;
SET @b = NULL;
SET @c = NULL;
PREPARE prepare_query FROM 'SELECT t0.c0 FROM t0, t1 WHERE ((?)OR(((((?)<=>(t1.c0)))AND(((?)<=>(t1.c0))))))';
EXECUTE prepare_query USING @a,@b,@c; -- interface conversion: expression.Expression is *expression.Constant, not *expression.ScalarFunction
```

Furthermore, after this error, the connection will be lost. For example, if there are statements after the EXECUTE statement, will trigger `Lost connection to MySQL server during query`

### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)

No error.

### 3. What did you see instead (Required)

```
interface conversion: expression.Expression is *expression.Constant, not *expression.ScalarFunction
```

